# Mjolnirsoft local environment configuration (template).
#
# ./setup.sh copies this file to .local.env on first run. .local.env is
# gitignored and machine-specific; this .example file is the checked-in
# template. Values are loaded at CLI startup by src/cli/load-local-env.ts;
# a real environment variable of the same name takes precedence.
#
# The automated executor (`--auto`) shells out to the `claude` CLI, which must be
# installed and logged in (it runs on your Claude Code subscription; no API key).

# CLAUDE_BIN — absolute path to the `claude` executable. Optional: only needed
# when `claude` isn't on the executor subprocess's PATH (a common Windows gap).
# When unset, the executor spawns `claude` (or `claude.exe` on Windows) from PATH.
# Example (Windows / WinGet install):
# CLAUDE_BIN=C:\Users\you\AppData\Local\Microsoft\WinGet\Packages\Anthropic.ClaudeCode_Microsoft.Winget.Source_8wekyb3d8bbwe\claude.exe

# NODE_BIN — absolute path to the `node` executable. Optional: only needed when
# `node` isn't on the Bash tool's PATH (a common Windows gap — the agent shell
# doesn't always inherit the interactive PATH). When unset, rebuild-extension.sh
# tries `node`/`node.exe` from PATH, then falls back to the common Windows install
# location (/c/Program Files/nodejs/node.exe).
# Example (Windows default Node.js install):
# NODE_BIN=/c/Program Files/nodejs/node.exe
